Step 1: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit ÷ Total Revenue) × 100
• Gross Profit = 1,535,951.24 
• Total Revenue = 7,825,951.24
• Calculation: 1,535,951.24 ÷ 7,825,951.24 = 0.1963 (approximately)
• Converting to percentage: 0.1963 × 100 = 19.63%

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities ÷ Total Current Liabilities
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -4,398,760.38 
• Total Current Liabilities = 2,491,297.55
• Calculation: -4,398,760.38 ÷ 2,491,297.55 ≈ -1.765, which rounds to -1.77

Thus, the answer in the required JSON format is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "19.63%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-1.77"
  }
}
